pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2346.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I wish they would fix poison by...</span><hr size=1> Redoing poisons so they are like potions, instead of the wierd coding they use now.<br><br>Just make them into expendable items that can only be activated by rogues(they can already do this).<br><br>The effects would simply give you a proc buff like rangers or SKs can cast on themselves.  The effects would last like 2 minutes and the proc would be whatever the poisons effect would be.<br><br>I think this would solve alot of the problems with poisons.  Sure, your not as precise as far as activation goes.  But I'm pretty certain I'll get at least 1 proc in any given fight.<br><br>This would also allow for stacking because they could add a pottered beaker or something that allowed us to combine 5 or 10 poisons into 1 multicharged poison just like potions.<br><br>Apply poison could still be implimented as like a channeling skill that works for when your activating the poison.<br><br>Just my opinion.  Easy to code to except the Apply as channeling thing.  Since just making them rogue only poisons in thinner bottels is pretty simple. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/uiceisfun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IceIsFun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/3/02 8:42:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2346.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I wish they would fix poison by...</span><hr size=1> What would really fix poisons is removing the snare component from the poisons that slow/snare. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47447">[60 Assassin] Yakita (Barbarian)</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/upherret.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pherret</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/3/02 11:34:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2346.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I wish they would fix poison by...</span><hr size=1> The thing is, there are plenty of other stuff they are working on and they are happy with where the rogue class is.  They won't be fixing poisons for a while, if not ever.<br><br>It's funny.  I save those slow poisons for those times when there is no slower for named mobs and either it fails to apply or it wears out in 2 ticks.  =P  Completely useless.<br><br>Also, at 250 skill... should I still be failing on a poison with 32 trivial?  I wish they would make it so if you have a 250 skill in something, you stop failing on trivials. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=15538" target="_blank">Pherret</a> - the other white meat.<SUP><font size="1">TM</font></SUP></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/urestyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Restyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/3/02 12:51:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2346.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.magelo.com/res/eq/itemicon/0307.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I wish they would fix poison by...</span><hr size=1> This topic has been discussed many times here. I agree with Perret. I don't think we will see any major changes ever in poisons. However, I still hold to the belief that several minor changes would help us all; increased drop rates on Tier I ingredients, all poison vendors carry all store bought ingredients; a couple new smithing recipes that include poison.<br><br>just my 2cp <p><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/pimp.gif><br><font color=red><b>Restyn</b><br>Rogue of Saryrn Server<br></font><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=262897><i><b>Half elf ... all rogue</b></i></a><br><font size=1 color=999999><I>Master Potter (154), Master Fletcher (139), Master Baker (139), Master Apothecary (120), Master Smith (117), Tailor (82), Brewer (65) and Friend to all Fish (3)</I></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/usemvarin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Semvarin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/3/02 1:13:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2346.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I wish they would fix poison by...</span><hr size=1> I did a feedback the other night on how to fix poison.  Now I've done many, about 23 total, and I doubt any have been read.  Last night I did a feedback on the idea of an endless vial skill.  When a rogue hits a certain skill I said 250, the poison would be applied and the vial would not be used up.  This eliminates the issue with poison vials not stacking, they don't need to, and allows for poisons to be useful in every day grouping.  It would allow a rogue to carry a backpack full of poisons one vial of each type, and reward those who maxed their skill.<br><br>The idea doesn't seem overly unbalancing, and should be an easy code change to implement.  What do you guys think about it? <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=85280">Semvarin Bignbeefy Assassin <Last Hope></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/ul0z.showPublicProfile?language=EN>L0z</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/5/02 1:11:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2346.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.douglasdesign.org/EQfiles/loz.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I wish they would fix poison by...</span><hr size=1> I think we'll see a change in poison making. There have been some good ideas tossed around here, and to Verant. I think we'll see a change if not before PoP, then when it comes out.<br><br>But that could just be my weird intuition. <p><table width="35%" border="0" height="59"><tr><td height="48"><div align="center"><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#C0C0C0"><b>Lozoria Shinkicker<br></b>Hobbit Assassin<br></font><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a style="text-decoration : none; color : #FFCC99" href="http://www.guildparadigm.org"><font color="#0080FF">Paradigm</font></a> | <a style="text-decoration : none; color : #FFCC99" href="mailto:jettat@douglasdesign.org"><font color="#0080FF">E-mail</font></a> | <a style="text-decoration : none; color : #FFCC99" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104742"><font color="#0080FF">Profile</font></a></font></