e=EN>Ravenwinged Angel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/10/02 10:32:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2346.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I wish they would fix poison by...</span><hr size=1> I think they would have to be reapplied in the middle of a fight like Vindicator(well, not Vindi, it doesn't take 2 minutes to kill Vindi on my server, maybe some of the other high hp mobs).  15 minutes of proccing on one poison?  As a rogue with a high dex, I can get alot of proc off in 2 minutes.<br><br>Thats just my opinion though, 2 minutes would be balanced with the effects they have currently.<br><br>I mean, if you had 15 minute poison procs, there would be no reason to make them stackable or charged. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujulesbrown.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jules Brown</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/11/02 10:02:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2346.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I wish they would fix poison by...</span><hr size=1> No, procs suck and can't be counted on.  The greatest use of our poisons, such as the slow or resist debuffs, is an EARLY application of the effect.<br><br>Changing poisons to random procs would totally ruin even that last aspect of usefulness for poisons.  You want procs, get a weapon with the proc you like.<br><br>Poisons should be improved by:<br>1.  Getting rid of the farmed components (more like alchemy)<br>2.  Some way to get charges on poisons (stacks of 20, whatever)<br>3.  Adding more USEFUL, STACKABLE, effects.<br>4.  Allowing for poison re-application without sitting (maybe as an AA) <p><a href ="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=3194">Jules, 60 pal</a>  [<a href="http://pub22.ezboard.com/bdaevents">Dark Advocates</a>] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=157332">Capones, 54 rog</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ublusco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Blusco</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/16/02 1:42:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2346.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I wish they would fix poison by...</span><hr size=1> My situation is that <br>1) poisons are useless except in very specific situations<br>and<br>2) it takes a lot of inventory space to support them<br><br>I know Verant have said they'll never put bags with more than 10 slots into the game, but I'd still love to see a 20-slot "Toxicologist's Satchel" that would only hold poison-related items. That might be different to write, so they could compromise by making it only hold TINY items (which vials, suspensions, reagents and finished product should all be anyway). <p><TABLE CELLSPACING=2, CELLPADDING=2 WIDTH=90% ALIGN="center"><TR><TD VALIGN="top">	<SPAN STYLE="font:11pt tahoma, verdana, arial, sans serif; color:#333399; font-weight:bold;">Blusco Kickshaw-Stonefoot</SPAN><BR>	<SPAN STYLE="font:7pt tahoma, verdana, arial, sans serif;">		Enraged an